The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Gang robs store cash, fires at safety staff
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Gang robs store cash, fires at safety staff
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Midnapore, Aug. 13: Robbers snatched Rs 39 lakh from a car carrying cash from a department store to a bank today, and shot and injured a security official before escaping on their motorbikes.        
	Police said the gang of six had intercepted the car 500 metres from the Big Bazaar outlet in Kharagpur around 1.30pm.         
	They forced the four occupants  the driver, two officials of a Calcutta-based security agency, and a security guard  to step out of the car, a police officer said.        
	The security guard dropped his gun accidentally while getting off the car. When he tried to pick it up, one of the gang members fired at him. However, he missed and the bullet hit one of the officials of the security agency, the officer added.        
	The gang then grabbed the leather bag containing the cash and sped off on their three motorbikes towards Nimpura, a locality on the outskirts of Kharagpur town.        
	Sandhodeep Bhattacharya, who took a bullet in the chest, is in hospital. Doctors said the bullet would have to be removed through surgery but added that the patient was out of danger.                                                                                                                                                            
